description.narrative: The Project Development Objective is to strengthen the financial and operational management of the National Health Insurance Scheme by improving: (i) the policy adaptation and implementation capacity of the National Health Insurance Council in addressing ongoing core policy issues related to contribution collection, risk equalization, and provider payment mechanisms; and (ii) the purchasing function of the District Mutual Health Insurance Schemes, and the billing function of the Providers.

condition.narrative: No later than Nov 1 of each year, NHIC will prepare and furnish an annual work plan detailing eligible activities and expendituresunder the Project for following FY
Not later than 6 months after Effective Date, NHIS to appoint independent financial and procurement auditors
Provider beneficiaries will enterinto an MOU with the NHIC that they will set aside sufficientfinds to allow for maintenance,replacement and future upgrades of depreciated stock
The recipient shall maintain, at all times, during the implementation of the Project, a positive 5 year forward looking actuarialbalance on the NHIS
